
# Cursor Rules: Modular Dashboard OS (Core LTS + Modules)

[Project]
Name: Modular Dashboard OS
Description: Static SPA with a stable Core (LTS) and module-based themes/features. Core exposes slots, registry, admin scaffold, theme tokens, storage, and events. All functionality resides in modules. Updates are delivered as module-only diffs.

[NonNegotiables]
- Adhere to Module API v1.1 (meta/init/mount/unmount/adminSections).
- Use CSS-safe IDs for admin sections and DOM nodes (letters, numbers, underscore, hyphen). No dots.
- ASCII-only source. No optional chaining (?.) or nullish coalescing (??).
- Token-first CSS. Themes define tokens; features consume tokens; core base.css is structural.
- Always load modules via dynamic import with new URL(url, document.baseURI).href.
- Must serve over HTTP. Do not rely on file://.
- Minimal diffs: return only necessary code changes unless a full file is explicitly requested.
- No third-party runtime deps or CDNs for MVP.


[Instructions]
-  Use and docs/roadmap.md as needed during the development process.
-  scope using the docs/Modular_Dashboard_OS_TRD.md 
-  create a handoff.md document at the end of each session when prompted to "end Session" that creates a prompt to continue where we left off for the next session.

[Files Structure]
- Consitent standardized file structure.
- all generated documents that not being used in the program go to a non-implemented directory.
- all documentation to a documenation directory


[Core-LTS]
Stable Slots (do not rename/remove):
- slot-header, slot-topbar, slot-quickbar
- slot-main (contains slot-favorites, slot-widgets)
- slot-overlays, slot-admin

Core Owns:
- appCtx (events, storage, theme), registry, admin scaffold, theme switching, stable slots, structural CSS.
Core Does NOT Own:
- Feature logic, heavy visuals, or module-specific CSS.

[Module-API]
Each module must export default with:
- meta: { name, label, version, kind('feature'|'theme') }
- async init(ctx), mount(ctx), unmount(ctx)
- adminSections(ctx) -> [{ tab, id (CSS-safe), title, hint, render(el, ctx) }]
Theme modules provide tokens only (no JS behavior beyond exposing or injecting tokens).

[Storage]
- LocalStorage only; keys must be namespaced as: mod:<kind>.<shortname>:data.
- Wrap read/write in try/catch; JSON-safe.

[Admin]
- Build tabs from adminSections() after init().
- On tab select: call section.render(el, ctx).
- Render failures: show visible inline error and console.error stack.
- Keyboard: Alt+A toggles Admin.

[Quality]
- Add brief rationale + manual test steps with every change.
- Keep functions small, imperative, framework-free.
- Avoid silent failures; log with clear module prefixes.

[UpdatePolicy]
- Ship changes as module diffs only.
- Do not modify Core LTS unless explicitly asked and approved (version bump).
- If a Core change is necessary, isolate to the smallest patch and document the contract impact.

[Backup]
- Backup is module agnostic; works even if a module has been added or removed, or re-added.
- Daily or weekly auto backups.
- Exportable JSON files for backup or moving to another PC.

[Security]
- No eval or remote code execution.
- Iframes: set sandbox/referrerpolicy/allowfullscreen; show message if blocked by CSP/XFO.

[Delivery]
- Use the established folder structure.
- New modules go under /modules/<kind>/<name>/.
- Themes under /modules/themes/<themeName>/.
